8\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 19:33 AR-029\n","metadata":{"output":"total 124\ndrwxr-xr-x 31 root root 4096 Apr 11 19:29 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 23 root root 4096 Apr 11 19:28 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:42 AR-001\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:55 AR-002\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 01:18 AR-003\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 01:50 AR-004\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 02:40 AR-005\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 03:17 AR-006\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 04:02 AR-007\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 04:39 AR-008\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 05:39 AR-009\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 06:14 AR-010\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 06:55 AR-011\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:34 AR-012\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 08:09 AR-013\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 08:50 AR-014\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 09:30 AR-015\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 10:54 AR-016\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:18 AR-017\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 12:11 AR-018\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 12:31 AR-019\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 13:21 AR-020\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 14:10 AR-021\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 14:26 AR-022\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 15:13 AR-023\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 15:59 AR-024\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 16:32 AR-025\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 17:41 AR-026\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 18:03 AR-027\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 18:48 AR-028\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 19:33 AR-029\n","exit":0,"description":"List changes directory","truncated":false},"title":"List changes directory","time":{"start":1775907598629,"end":1775907598652}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907598668,"sessionID":"ses_283a8f1b8ffeuMAM0MLnXzGmgw","part":{"id":"prt_d7c5763ee001X6M2CaM5600rG8","messageID":"msg_d7c5745cc001I4V8Swzz3BNEW7","sessionID":"ses_283a8f1b8ffeuMAM0MLnXzGmgw","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI Binary Entry (4 binaries) - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-019\n6: **Module:** `cmd`\n7: **Language:** Go\n8: **Size:** M\n9: **Base Spec:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n10: \n11: AR-019 implements the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components: `agentd` (idle cleanup controller), `router` (session routing), `workload-manager` (sandbox orchestration), and `picod` (sandbox daemon). Each binary SHALL parse CLI flags, initialize configuration, wire dependencies, and start the respective service with graceful shutdown handling.\n12: \n13: The base spec defines the client-go library for API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` with `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` types.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Requirements\n18: \n19: ### Requirement: Binary Entry Point Structure\n20: \n21: The system SHALL provide 4 binary entry points under `cmd/`: `cmd/agentd/main.go`, `cmd/router/main.go`, `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`, and `cmd/picod/main.go`. Each SHALL use standard Go flag parsing with sensible defaults and support graceful shutdown via OS signal handling.\n22: \n23: #### Scenario: Binary compiles successfully\n24: - **GIVEN** the `cmd/` directory contains the 4 binary entry point files\n25: - **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/agentd/... && go build ./cmd/router/... && go build ./cmd/workload-manager/... && go build ./cmd/picod/...` is executed\n26: - **THEN** all 4 binaries SHALL compile without errors\n27: - **AND** the output binaries SHALL be runnable with `--help` flag\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Binary prints help\n30: - **GIVEN** any of the 4 binaries is built\n31: - **WHEN** the binary is executed with `--help` flag\n32: - **THEN** it SHALL print usage information including available flags\n33: - **AND** it SHALL exit with code 0\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Agentd Binary Entry Point\n38: \n39: The `cmd/agentd/main.go` SHALL parse flags for Kubernetes configuration, construct a controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `runtimev1alpha1` (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter), disable metrics and health probe servers, and run the idle cleanup reconciler.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Agentd starts with default flags\n42: - **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n43: - **AND** flags include `--kubeconfig` (optional, default: in-cluster), `--sync-period` (default: 5m)\n44: - **WHEN** the binary starts without arguments in a cluster environment\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL construct manager with in-cluster config\n46: - **AND** it SHALL register the reconciler for `AgentRuntime` resources\n47: - **AND** it SHALL start the reconciler with 5-minute sync period\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Agentd handles graceful shutdown\n50: - **GIVEN** agentd is running with controller-runtime manager\n51: - **WHEN** SIGINT or SIGTERM is received\n52: - **THEN** it SHALL gracefully stop the manager\n53: - **AND** it SHALL exit with code 0\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: Router Binary Entry Point\n58: \n59: The `cmd/router/main.go` SHALL parse flags for HTTP port, debug mode, Redis/Valkey connection, session store configuration, and backend workload manager endpoint. It SHALL construct a Gin HTTP server with session routing middleware.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Router starts with default flags\n62: - **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n63: - **AND** flags include `--port` (default: 8080), `--debug` (default: false), `--redis-addr` (required), `--workload-manager` (required)\n64: - **WHEN** the binary starts with required flags provided\n65: - **THEN** it SHALL construct Gin router with session middleware\n66: - **AND** it SHALL listen on the specified port\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: Router validates required flags\n69: - **GIVEN** router binary is built\n70: - **WHEN** started without required flags (`--redis-addr` or `--workload-manager`)\n71: - **THEN** it SHALL print error message indicating missing flags\n72: - **AND** it SHALL exit with non-zero code\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: Workload Manager Binary Entry Point\n77: \n78: The `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` SHALL parse flags for HTTP port, Kubernetes config, Redis/Valkey connection, and resource defaults. It SHALL construct the workload manager with controller for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs and HTTP API server.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Workload manager starts with default flags\n81: - **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n82: - **AND** flags include `--port` (default: 8080), `--kubeconfig` (optional), `--redis-addr` (required)\n83: - **WHEN** the binary starts with required flags provided\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL construct the workload manager controller for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` types\n85: - **AND** it SHALL start the HTTP API server on the specified port\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Workload manager registers CRD schemes\n88: - **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` initializes the controller-runtime manager\n89: - **WHEN** the scheme is being configured\n90: - **THEN** it SHALL register `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` types from `runtimev1alpha1`\n91: - **AND** it SHALL use REST resource plurals `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` as defined in base spec\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: Picod Binary Entry Point\n96: \n97: The `cmd/picod/main.go` SHALL parse flags for HTTP port and workspace root. It SHALL construct the picod server with code execution, file upload/download, and exec streaming capabilities.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Picod starts with default flags\n100: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n101: - **AND** flags include `--port` (default: 8080), `--workspace` (default: current directory)\n102: - **WHEN** the binary starts\n103: - **THEN** it SHALL resolve workspace to absolute path\n104: - **AND** it SHALL start the HTTP server with code execution handlers\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Picod validates workspace\n107: - **GIVEN** picod binary is built\n108: - **WHEN** started with `--workspace=/nonexistent/path`\n109: - **THEN** it SHALL attempt to create the directory\n110: - **AND** if creation fails, it SHALL log fatal error and exit\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## Interface\n115: \n116: ### Binary: agentd\n117: \n118: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n119: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n120: | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig file (empty for in-cluster) |\n121: | `--sync-period` | duration | 5m | Period for full sync of all AgentRuntimes |\n122: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n123: \n124: ### Binary: router\n125: \n126: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n127: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n128: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n129: | `--debug` | bool | false | Enable debug mode with request logging |\n130: | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | Redis/Valkey server address (required) |\n131: | `--workload-manager` | string | \"\" | Workload manager endpoint URL (required) |\n132: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n133: \n134: ### Binary: workload-manager\n135: \n136: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n137: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n138: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n139: | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig file (empty for in-cluster) |\n140: | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | Redis/Valkey server address (required) |\n141: | `--default-namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default namespace for AgentRuntimes |\n142: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n143: \n144: ### Binary: picod\n145: \n146: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n147: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n148: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n149: | `--workspace` | string | \".\" | Workspace root directory |\n150: | `--read-header-timeout` | duration | 10s | HTTP read header timeout |\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Behavior\n155: \n156: ### Common Behavior\n157: \n158: All 4 binaries SHALL:\n159: 1. Parse flags using Go's `flag` package\n160: 2. Log startup message with version and flag values (except secrets)\n161: 3. Handle SIGINT/SIGTERM for graceful shutdown\n162: 4. Return exit code 0 on clean shutdown, non-zero on fatal errors\n163: 5. Support `--help` to print usage and exit cleanly\n164: \n165: ### Graceful Shutdown Sequence\n166: \n167: ```\n168: 1. Receive SIGINT/SIGTERM\n169: 2. Log \"Shutting down gracefully...\"\n170: 3. Create context with timeout (graceful-timeout)\n171: 4. Call server/manager Shutdown() with timeout context\n172: 5. Wait for shutdown or timeout\n173: 6. If timeout exceeded, log warning and force exit\n174: 7. Exit with code 0 (or 1 if timeout exceeded)\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ## Changes to Base Specification\n180: \n181: This AR consumes the client-go library defined in `deployment/client-go.md`. The following types from the base spec are used:\n182: \n183: | Type | Package | Usage |\n184: |------|---------|-------|\n185: | `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` | `client-go` | Resource reconciled by workload-manager |\n186: | `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` | `client-go` | Resource reconciled by workload-manager |\n187: | `versioned.Interface` | `client-go/clientset/versioned` | Kubernetes client interface |\n188: | `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` | `client-go/typed/runtime/v1alpha1` | Typed client for runtime group |\n189: \n190: No modifications to the base client-go interfaces.\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ## Dependencies\n195: \n196: | Package | Purpose |\n197: |---------|---------|\n198: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Agentd/workload-manager manager construction |\n199: | `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd` | Kubernetes config loading |\n200: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Router HTTP framework |\n201: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n202: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n203: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Base spec: generated Kubernetes client |\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## File Index\n208: \n209: | Path | Purpose |\n210: |------|---------|\n211: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Agentd binary entry point |\n212: | `cmd/router/main.go` | Router binary entry point |\n213: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Workload manager binary entry point |\n214: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Picod binary entry point |\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## Testing\n219: \n220: ### Scenario: All binaries compile\n221: ```bash\n222: go build ./cmd/agentd/... && \\\n223: go build ./cmd/router/... && \\\n224: go build ./cmd/workload-manager/... && \\\n225: go build ./cmd/picod/...\n226: ```\n227: **Expected:** All commands succeed with no output (or warnings only).\n228: \n229: ### Scenario: All binaries print help\n230: ```bash\n231: ./agentd --help\n232: ./router --help\n233: ./workload-manager --help\n234: ./picod --help\n235: ```\n236: **Expected:** Each prints flag usage and exits with code 0.\n237: \n238: ### Scenario: Graceful shutdown test\n239: ```bash\n240: timeout 2 ./agentd --sync-period=1s &\n241: sleep 0.5\n242: kill %1\n243: wait %1\n244: echo \"Exit code: $?\"\n245: ```\n246: **Expected:** Exit code is 0 after graceful shutdown message.\n247: \n248: ### Scenario: Workload manager scheme registration\n249: ```bash\n250: # Verify workload-manager can initialize with CRD scheme\n251: ./workload-manager --redis-addr=localhost:6379 --kubeconfig=/dev/null 2>&1 | head -5\n252: ```\n253: **Expected:** Error should relate to connection, not scheme registration.\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## Deliverables\n258: \n259: | Path | Description |\n260: |------|-------------|\n261: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Agentd binary entry point with AgentRuntime reconciler |\n262: | `cmd/router/main.go` | Router binary entry point with Gin and session routing |\n263: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Workload manager with AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter controller |\n264: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Picod binary entry point with workspace handling |\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: *AR-019 — Module: cmd — Language: Go — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 268 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry (4 binaries) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-019\n**Module:** `cmd`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** M\n**Base Spec:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n\nAR-019 implements the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components: `agentd` (idle cleanup controller), `router` (session routing), `workload-manager` (sandbox orchestration), and `picod` (sandbox daemon). Each binary SHALL parse CLI flags, initialize configuration, wire dependencies, and start the respective service with graceful shutdown handling.\n\nThe base spec defines the client-go library for API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` with `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` types.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Binary Entry Point Structure\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775907598616,"end":1775907598665}}}}
