{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907905237,"sessionID":"ses_283a8f1b8ffeuMAM0MLnXzGmgw","part":{"id":"prt_d7c58296e001vRz6Ny4M341OiV","messageID":"msg_d7c57ca8e0015jkmAQSchXrFex","sessionID":"ses_283a8f1b8ffeuMAM0MLnXzGmgw","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-029  \n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\nAR-029 implements the low-level HTTP client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK. This includes the `ControlPlaneClient` for Workload Manager API communication, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Router data plane operations, and supporting utilities for HTTP session management, authentication, and timeout handling.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: HTTP Session Factory\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `create_session` utility function that constructs a `requests.Session` with connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` protocols.\n\n#### Scenario: Session created with default pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is constructed\n- **THEN** it SHALL mount HTTPAdapter for both protocols with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n#### Scenario: Session created with custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is called\n- **WHEN** the session is constructed\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided pool configuration values\n\n#### Scenario: Session reused for multiple requests\n- **GIVEN** a session created by `create_session()`\n- **WHEN** multiple HTTP requests are made through the same session\n- **THEN** connections SHALL be reused from the pool\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Control Plane HTTP Client\n\nThe system SHALL implement `ControlPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` for Workload Manager API communication using `requests.Session` with connection pooling.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session POST request\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\": \"...\", \"namespace\": \"...\", \"ttl\": ..., \"metadata\": ...}`\n- **AND** it SHALL return `data[\"sessionId\"]` from the response\n- **AND** if `sessionId` is missing, it SHALL raise `ValueError`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session with 404 handling\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)` is called\n- **WHEN** the server returns 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (idempotent behavior)\n- **AND** on other failures, it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL resolution\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` argument is not provided\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n\n#### Scenario: Authentication token resolution\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` argument is not provided\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL attempt to read token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`\n- **AND** if token is non-empty, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header on the session\n\n#### Scenario: Default headers on session\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `Content-Type: application/json` as a default header\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout tuple on requests\n- **GIVEN** `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0`\n- **WHEN** any request is made\n- **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, timeout)` = `(5.0, 120)`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Code Interpreter Data Plane HTTP Client\n\nThe system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` for Router data plane operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL construction from router URL\n- **GIVEN** `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name` are provided\n- **WHEN** `base_url` is not explicitly provided\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct base URL as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command POST\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}api/execute` with JSON body `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`\n- **AND** if `exit_code != 0` in response, raise `CommandExecutionError`\n\n#### Scenario: Execute timeout buffer\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with `timeout=60`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `60 + 2.0 = 62.0` seconds (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n\n#### Scenario: Write file POST\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": \"...\", \"content\": \"base64...\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}api/files` with multipart/form-data\n- **AND** include `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path': ..., 'mode': '0644'}`\n- **AND** include `x-agentcube-session-id` header explicitly (no JSON Content-Type on outer request)\n\n#### Scenario: Download file GET\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET {base_url}api/files/{clean_path}` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n- **AND** use `stream=True` for the response\n\n#### Scenario: List files GET\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\".\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET {base_url}api/files?path={path}`\n\n#### Scenario: Session header on all requests\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with `session_id`\n- **WHEN** any `_request` method is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Agent Runtime Data Plane HTTP Client\n\nThe system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` for Agent Runtime Router invocations.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL construction\n- **GIVEN** `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name` are provided\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct base URL as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID\n- **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET {base_url}` and read response header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **AND** if the header is missing, raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke POST with headers\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}` with:\n  - Header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n  - Header `Content-Type: application/json`\n  - JSON body from `payload` dict\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout` argument\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n\n#### Scenario: SESSION_HEADER constant\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n- **WHEN** accessing the class constant\n- **THEN** `SESSION_HEADER` SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Timeout Behavior\n\nThe system SHALL implement consistent timeout defaults across all HTTP clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane default timeouts\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout overrides\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** connect timeout SHALL default to `5.0` seconds\n- **AND** read timeout SHALL default to `120` seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane default timeouts\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` or `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout overrides\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** connect timeout SHALL default to `5.0` seconds\n- **AND** read timeout SHALL default to `120` seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Per-request timeout override\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=30)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is made\n- **THEN** the effective read timeout SHALL be `30 + 2.0 = 32.0` seconds\n- **AND** the PicoD timeout string SHALL be `\"30s\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor timeout override\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0)` is constructed\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called without timeout argument\n- **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(3.0, 60)`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session Header Management\n\nThe system SHALL consistently use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Router data plane requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header default\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with `session_id`\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the default headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n\n#### Scenario: Agent Runtime session header constant\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n- **WHEN** the `SESSION_HEADER` constant is used\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Upload sets header explicitly\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file` performs a multipart upload\n- **WHEN** the request is constructed\n- **THEN** the `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be set explicitly on the request (not relying on session defaults)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Connection Pool Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support configurable connection pooling for all HTTP clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Default pool configuration\n- **GIVEN** any HTTP client is initialized without pool overrides\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** `pool_connections` SHALL default to `10`\n- **AND** `pool_maxsize` SHALL default to `10`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom pool configuration\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is constructed\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the HTTPAdapter SHALL be configured with the custom pool settings\n\n#### Scenario: Pool settings passed through create_session\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is called\n- **WHEN** the session is returned\n- **THEN** the underlying adapter pool SHALL reflect these settings\n\n---\n\n## Interface\n\n### ControlPlaneClient\n\n| Method | Parameters | Returns | Description |\n|--------|------------|---------|-------------|\n| `__init__` | `workload_manager_url=None, auth_token=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0, pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Initialize with URL/auth resolution |\n| `create_session` | `name=\"my-interpreter\", namespace=\"default\", metadata=None, ttl=3600` | `str` | POST to create session, return sessionId |\n| `delete_session` | `session_id: str` | `bool` | DELETE session, True on success/404 |\n| `close` | - | `None` | Close the HTTP session |\n\n### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n| Method | Parameters | Returns | Description |\n|--------|------------|---------|-------------|\n| `__init__` | `session_id, router_url=None, namespace=None, cr_name=None, base_url=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0, pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Initialize with session and URL |\n| `_request` | `method, endpoint, body=None, **kwargs` | `Response` | Internal request method with headers |\n| `execute_command` | `command, timeout=None` | `str` | POST api/execute, return stdout |\n| `run_code` | `language, code, timeout=None` | `str` | Write file and execute |\n| `write_file` | `content, remote_path` | `None` | POST api/files with base64 content |\n| `upload_file` | `local_path, remote_path` | `None` | POST multipart api/files |\n| `download_file` | `remote_path, local_path` | `None` | GET api/files/{path} with streaming |\n| `list_files` | `path=\".\"` | `Any` | GET api/files?path={path} |\n| `close` | - | `None` | Close the HTTP session |\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n| Method | Parameters | Returns | Description |\n|--------|------------|---------|-------------|\n| `__init__` | `router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0, pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Initialize with Router endpoint |\n| `bootstrap_session_id` | - | `str` | GET base URL, return session header |\n| `invoke` | `session_id, payload, timeout=None` | `Response` | POST JSON with session header |\n| `close` | - | `None` | Close the HTTP session |\n\n### Utility Functions\n\n| Function | Location | Parameters | Returns | Description |\n|----------|----------|------------|---------|-------------|\n| `create_session` | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10` | `Session` | Create requests.Session with adapters |\n| `read_token_from_file` | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `file_path: str` | `str` | Read file contents stripped, \"\" on error |\n\n---\n\n## Behavior\n\n### HTTP Request Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n│  Client Call    │────▶│  Prepare Request │────▶│  Apply Headers  │\n└─────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n                                                           │\n                           ┌──────────────────┐           │\n                           │  Parse Response  │◀──────────┘\n                           └──────────────────┘\n                                    │\n                           ┌────────┴────────┐\n                           ▼                 ▼\n                    ┌────────────┐    ┌────────────┐\n                    │  Success   │    │   Error    │\n                    │  Return    │    │  Raise/Log │\n                    │  Result    │    │  Exception │\n                    └────────────┘    └────────────┘\n```\n\n### Timeout Configuration Hierarchy\n\n1. **Per-call timeout**: Method argument (e.g., `execute_command(timeout=30)`)\n2. **Instance default**: Constructor value (e.g., `timeout=120`)\n3. **Global default**: Module constant (`DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120`)\n\n### Session Header Application\n\n| Client Type | Header Source | Applied Via |\n|-------------|---------------|-------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | N/A | Not used (auth via Authorization) |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Constructor `session_id` | Session default headers |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Method `session_id` arg | Per-request headers |\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Base Specification\n\nThis AR implements the HTTP client layer defined in `python-sdk/spec.md` sections:\n- HTTP client contracts — control plane\n- HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n- HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n- Session header management\n- Timeout behavior\n\nNo changes to base spec interfaces.\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `requests` | any | HTTP client library |\n| `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT token handling (for auth) |\n| `cryptography` | any | Crypto operations |\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` implementation |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` HTTP session factory |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` utility |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | `CommandExecutionError` and base exceptions |\n\n---\n\n## Testing\n\n### Unit Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: create_session with defaults\n```python\nsession = create_session()\nassert session.adapters[\"http://\"].config[\"pool_connections\"] == 10\nassert session.adapters[\"https://\"].config[\"pool_maxsize\"] == 10\n```\n\n#### Scenario: ControlPlaneClient creates session with correct timeout\n```python\nclient = ControlPlaneClient(timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0)\n# Verify session timeout tuple (3.0, 60) used in requests\n```\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base URL\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n    session_id=\"abc\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    cr_name=\"my-interpreter\"\n)\nassert client.base_url == \"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"\n```\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command timeout buffer\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"abc\", base_url=\"http://test\")\n# When execute_command(command, timeout=30) is called\n# Read timeout should be 32.0 seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n```\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap session\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\"\n)\nsession_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n# Should GET base URL and extract x-agentcube-session-id header\n```\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file multipart with session header\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"abc\", base_url=\"http://test\")\nclient.upload_file(\"local.txt\", \"/remote/path.txt\")\n# Should POST multipart with x-agentcube-session-id header\n```\n\n---\n\n## Deliverables\n\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Control plane HTTP client with session management |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Code Interpreter data plane HTTP client |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Agent Runtime data plane HTTP client |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | HTTP session factory with connection pooling |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Token file reading utility |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | CommandExecutionError exception class |\n\n---\n\n*AR-029 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775907905181,"end":1775907905234}}}}
